What you need to know:  Defending champions Menengai Oilers, runners-up Topfry Nakuru, KCB, Batuk, Nondescript, Machine, Masinde Muliro, Catholic Monks, Mwamba, USIU Martials and Blak Blad are some of the top teams expected to grace the eventEmbu RFC chairman Moses Mukabane said they were excited to roll out the event following a three-year hiatus due to Covid-19 pandemicKenya Rugby Union (KRU) Central region coordinator Patrick Mwika said Embu 7s was the largest event in the region, following the fall of the Meru 7s